DAMATURU – North East Youth Initiative for Development (NEYIF) under the leadership of Comrade. Dauda Gombe Muhammad,has concluded arrangements set to train 2,500 teachers of basic and secondary schools  in the state. The training is part of the Organization’s contribution towards complimenting the revitalization of the education sector of Governor Mai Mala Buni . The training,according to Gombe ,will cover areas such as; pedagogy, psycho-social support (PSS), disaster risk reduction and conflict sensitivity education. The NEYIF’s coordinator said:”A refresher training have since commence for Master Trainers who will then step down the training to teachers at various Local Government Headquarters”. He also said the training will be in three phases Gombe further said: “Let’s join hand to support the future generations of our citizens by improving quality of teaching and learning”.